{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62741f7a-ed33-414f-b6eb-ceddfd59fffd","content":"The directory appears to be empty — there's no workflow file here for me to modify. But here's what you need to change conceptually:\n\n### Switching to NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. GitHub Actions workflow changes:**\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n               --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} \\\n               --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write          # ← required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4   # v4+ supports trusted publishing\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n               --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n               # no --api-key needed!\n```\n\n**Key workflow changes:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write` to the job.\n- Use `actions/setup-dotnet@v4` (it handles the OIDC token exchange automatically).\n- **Remove** the `--api-key` / `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` reference.\n\n**2. NuGet.org configuration:**\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**.\n2. Add a new **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher, specifying:\n   - Repository owner & name\n   - Workflow filename (e.g., `publish.yml`)\n   - Optionally: environment, branch/tag filters\n3. Once configured, you can **delete** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo.\n\n**That's it** — NuGet.org will verify the OIDC token from your workflow instead of an API key, with no secrets to rotate.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ff9bf554-475c-4892-ab34-fb3b57e927f5","outputTokens":502},"id":"c45885e1-f00c-457b-8750-6759952c907d","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:37:06.666Z","parentId":"4dc990f6-23c6-418d-bf87-e65dd5afe5ee"}
